    "notes": [
      {
        "category": "summary",
        "text": "An update is available for nodejs-nodemon, nodejs, nodejs-packaging.\nThis update affects Rocky Linux 8.\nA Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVE list",
        "title": "Topic"
      },
      {
        "category": "description",
        "text": "Node.js is a software development platform for building fast and scalable network applications in the JavaScript programming language. \n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* npm: npm ci succeeds when package-lock.json doesn't match package.json (CVE-2021-43616)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.\n\nThis advisory is provided by Ctrl IQ, Inc for Rocky Linux systems. For more information about CIQ security practices, visit https://ciq.com/security.",
        "title": "Description"
      }
